def conv_batch(in_num, out_num, kernel_size=3, padding=1, stride=1):
    return nn.Sequential(
        nn.Conv2d(in_num, out_num, kernel_size=kernel_size, stride=stride, padding=padding, bias=False),
        nn.BatchNorm2d(out_num),
        nn.LeakyReLU())


# Residual block
class DarkResidualBlock(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, in_channels):
        super(DarkResidualBlock, self).__init__()

        reduced_channels = int(in_channels/2)

        self.layer1 = conv_batch(in_channels, reduced_channels, kernel_size=1, padding=0)
        self.layer2 = conv_batch(reduced_channels, in_channels)

    def forward(self, x):
        residual = x

        out = self.layer1(x)
        out = self.layer2(out)
        out += residual
        return out


class Darknet53(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, block):
        super(Darknet53, self).__init__()
        self.conv1 = conv_batch(3, 32)
        self.conv2 = conv_batch(32, 64, stride=2)
        self.residual_block1 = self.make_layer(block, in_channels=64, num_blocks=1)
        self.conv3 = conv_batch(64, 128, stride=2)
        self.residual_block2 = self.make_layer(block, in_channels=128, num_blocks=2)
        self.conv4 = conv_batch(128, 256, stride=2)
        self.residual_block3 = self.make_layer(block, in_channels=256, num_blocks=8)
        self.conv5 = conv_batch(256, 512, stride=2)
        self.residual_block4 = self.make_layer(block, in_channels=512, num_blocks=8)
        self.conv6 = conv_batch(512, 1024, stride=(3,2))
        self.residual_block5 = self.make_layer(block, in_channels=1024, num_blocks=4)
        self.maxpool2d = nn.MaxPool2d(3, stride=(3,2), padding=1)
        self.conv7 = conv_batch(1024, 5, stride=(1,2))
    def forward(self, x):
        out = self.conv1(x)
        out = self.conv2(out)
        out = self.residual_block1(out)
        out = self.conv3(out)
        out = self.residual_block2(out)
        out = self.conv4(out)
        out = self.residual_block3(out)
        out = self.conv5(out)
        out = self.residual_block4(out)
        out = self.conv6(out)
        out = self.residual_block5(out)
        out = self.maxpool2d(out)
        out = self.conv7(out)
        grid_width  = x.shape[2:][1]/out.shape[2:][1] # 128 = 1280/10
        grid_height = x.shape[2:][0]/out.shape[2:][0] # 144 =  720/5
        dx = torch.arange(out.shape[2:][1]) * grid_width  + grid_width//2  
        dy = torch.arange(out.shape[2:][0]) * grid_height + grid_height//2
        dx = dx.cuda() # [64., 192., 320., 448., 576., 704., 832., 960., 1088., 1216.]
        dy = dy.cuda() # [72., 216., 360., 504., 648.]
        c = out[0][0]
        x = out[0][1]
        y = out[0][2]
        h = out[0][3]
        w = out[0][4]
        c = torch.sigmoid(c)
        x = x * grid_width  + dx
        y = ((y * grid_height).T + dy).T
        h = h * grid_height
        w = w * grid_width
        out[0][0] = c
        out[0][1] = x - w/2
        out[0][2] = y - h/2
        out[0][3] = x + w/2
        out[0][4] = y + h/2
        out = torch.reshape(out, (1, 5, 50))
        out = out.permute(0, 2, 1)
        return out
    def make_layer(self, block, in_channels, num_blocks):
        layers = []
        for i in range(0, num_blocks):
            layers.append(block(in_channels))
        return nn.Sequential(*layers)


def darknet53():
    return Darknet53(DarkResidualBlock)

from scipy.optimize import linear_sum_assignment

W_conf = 0.98
W_loc  = 0.0032
W_pos  = 0.63
W_neg  = 0.37
MSE = torch.nn.MSELoss()

def positiveLoss(target, prediction):
    confidence_loss = -torch.log(prediction[0] + 0.0000001)
    location_loss = MSE(prediction[1:], target)
    return W_conf*confidence_loss + W_loc*location_loss

def negativeLoss(prediction):
    return -torch.log(1-prediction[:, 0] + 0.0000001)

def Loss(targets, predictions):
    len_predictions = len(predictions)
    len_targets = len(targets)
    a = torch.zeros(( len_targets, len_predictions )).cuda()
    for i in range(len_targets):
        for j in range(len_predictions):
            a[i][j] = positiveLoss(targets[i], predictions[j])
    row_ind, col_ind = linear_sum_assignment(a.detach().cpu().numpy())
    neg_idx = [ i for i in range(len_predictions) if i not in col_ind ]
    positive_loss = a[row_ind, col_ind]
    negative_loss = negativeLoss(predictions[neg_idx])
    total_loss = W_pos*positive_loss.mean() + W_neg*negative_loss.mean()
    return total_loss

def train(model, batch, optimizer):
    model.train()
    optimizer.zero_grad()
    inputs, labels = batch
    inputs = inputs.cuda()
    labels = labels.cuda()
    outputs = model(inputs)
    l = Loss(labels[0], outputs[0])
    l.backward()
    optimizer.step()
    return l

def evaluate(model, batch, optimizer):
    model.eval()
    inputs, labels = batch
    inputs = inputs.cuda()
    labels = labels.cuda()
    outputs = model(inputs)
    l = Loss(labels[0], outputs[0])
    return outputs[0], l

transforms = torchvision.transforms.Compose([
    torchvision.transforms.ToTensor(),
])

class ImageFolder(torch.utils.data.Dataset):
    def __init__(self, folder_path, transform=None):
        self.image_dir = folder_path
        self.x = sorted(os.listdir(self.image_dir+"/images"))
        self.y = sorted(os.listdir(self.image_dir+"/annots"))
        self.transform = transform
    def __getitem__(self, index):
        image_path = os.path.join(self.image_dir+"/images", self.x[index])  
        xml_path = os.path.join(self.image_dir+"/annots", self.y[index])
        labels = []
        root = ET.parse(xml_path).getroot()
        for bndbox in root.findall("object/bndbox"):
            labels.append((
                float(bndbox.find("xmin").text),
                float(bndbox.find("ymin").text),
                float(bndbox.find("xmax").text),
                float(bndbox.find("ymax").text),
            ))
        labels = torch.FloatTensor(labels)
        image = Image.open(image_path).convert("RGB")
        if self.transform:
            image = self.transform(image)
        return image, labels
    def get_image_path(self, index):
        image_path = os.path.join(self.image_dir+"/images", self.x[index])
        return image_path
    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.x)

train_dataset = ImageFolder("drive/MyDrive/DeepLearningAssignment4/train", transform=transforms)
valid_dataset = ImageFolder("drive/MyDrive/DeepLearningAssignment4/valid", transform=transforms)

optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=LEARNING_RATE)
epoches = 5
min_loss = 1000000

import progressbar # progressbar
for epoch in range(epoches):
    bar = progressbar.ProgressBar( \
          maxval=(len(train_loader)+len(valid_loader)), \
          widgets=[
            f'Epoch: {epoch + 1} - ', \
            progressbar.Percentage()
          ]) # progressbar
    n = 0 # progressbar

    loo1 = 0; d1 = 0
    for batch in train_loader:
        l = train(model, batch, optimizer)
        loo1 += l.item(); d1 += 1
        bar.update(n+1) # progressbar
        n += 1 # progressbar
    loo = 0; d = 0
    for batch in valid_loader:
        _pred_, l = evaluate(model, batch, optimizer)
        loo += l.item(); d += 1
        bar.update(n+1) # progressbar
        n += 1 # progressbar
    bar.finish() # progressbar
    
    if loo1/d1 > min_loss: 
        LEARNING_RATE *= 0.99
        print("- LEARNING_RATE = %f" % (LEARNING_RATE))
    min_loss = loo1/d1

    print("Train Loss: %.4f" % (loo1/d1))
    print("Valid Loss: %.4f" % (loo/d))
    print()

    torch.save(model.state_dict(), 'drive/MyDrive/DeepLearningAssignment4/model.pt')

def detec_image(dataset, index):
    one_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader([dataset[index]], batch_size=1, shuffle=False)
    batch = next(iter(one_loader))
    pred, l = evaluate(model, batch, optimizer)
    with Image.open(dataset.get_image_path(index)).convert("RGB") as im:
        draw = ImageDraw.Draw(im)
        for x in batch[1][0]:
            draw.rectangle(x.tolist(), width=3, outline=(0, 255, 0))
        pred = pred[pred[:, 0] > 0.99]
        for x in pred[:, 1:]:
            draw.rectangle(x.tolist(), width=3, outline=(255, 255, 0))
        image = im
    return image

detec_image(valid_dataset, 7)
